window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>You can listen to this comforting story for free on your device with the Audible Stories Skill. Just say “Alexa, read me a family story,” or “Alexa, read me a story” to hear more free genres.</b></p> <p>A crotchety nightwatchman in a whaling museum contemplates Neptune the stuffed sea lion, originally owned by P.T. Barnum. In his admiration for the kingly animal, he studies ventriloquism to give Neptune a voice. When a field trip comes through the museum, he has an unexpectedly meaningful exchange with a precocious, like-minded child...and Neptune.</p> <p>Annie Hartnett is the author of the novels <i>Rabbit Cake </i>and <i>Unlikely Animals</i>. Rabbit Cake was listed as one of <i>Kirkus Reviews</i>' Best Books of 2017 and was <i>People </i>magazine's Book of the Week. Annie has been awarded fellowships and residencies from the MacDowell Colony, Sewanee Writers' Conference, and the Associates of the Boston Public Library. She holds degrees from the MFA program at the University of Alabama, Middlebury College's Bread Loaf School of English, and Hamilton College. She lives in Massachusetts with her husband, daughter, and dog.</p>"; 
